While the traction problem in elastostatics is linearization unstable, it is formally obvious that the dynamic problem is linearization stable. This remark, due to Capriz and Podio-Guidugli [1974], may be comforting to those who are uneasy about linearization instabilities, but the traction problem is tantalizing nonetheless. Linearization stability is discussed in general terms in Section 4.4, and the traction problem is examined in Section 7.3.

