(c) Local transformation properties. We can use the transformation rules for vectors found in Section 1.1 to define a local vector in a coordinate chart as a vector in IR" and then use the coordinate transformation rules to define an equivalence relation on pairs of charts and local vectors. Each equivalence class obtained is a tangent vector to ;m (see Lang [1972], pp. 26, 47).
